-- Garnett Fined $25,000 for Shunning Media After Being Eliminated
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2012-06-13T19:52:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-13/garnett-fined-25-000-for-shunning-media-after-being-eliminated.html
Boston Celtics forward  Kevin Garnett 
was fined $25,000 for failing to make himself available to the
media after the team was eliminated by the Miami Heat in Game 7
of the Eastern Conference Finals, the National Basketball
Association said in a statement.  Miami beat Boston 101-88 on June 9.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  